WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.265 --> 00:00:06.353
<i>Previously on
"The Hunting Party"...</i>

2
00:00:06.354 --> 00:00:07.876
<i>It's called The Pit.</i>

3
00:00:07.877 --> 00:00:09.399
<i>It's home to the most dangerous
and violent criminals</i>

4
00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:11.793
<i>in history. all of whom
the world believes are dead.</i>

5
00:00:11.794 --> 00:00:15.753
<i>Or at least it was
until the blast hit.</i>

6
00:00:15.754 --> 00:00:17.277
<i>Shane deserved
to know the truth.</i>

7
00:00:17.278 --> 00:00:18.495
<i>What are you going to tell him?</i>

8
00:00:18.496 --> 00:00:20.019
<i>Hey. we found your
serial killer mom.</i>

9
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.368
and she happens to be our boss?

10
00:00:21.369 --> 00:00:23.065
I don't know.
but I'll find the right words.

11
00:00:23.066 --> 00:00:24.893
You were impressive.

12
00:00:24.894 --> 00:00:26.590
Thank you. sir.

13
00:00:26.591 --> 00:00:28.766
And my name's John. by the way.

14
00:00:28.767 --> 00:00:30.594
Jonathan Mitchell Peck.

15
00:00:30.595 --> 00:00:31.726
I read your file.

16
00:00:31.727 --> 00:00:33.249
I've been thinking
a lot about that.

17
00:00:33.250 --> 00:00:35.121
and I should never have kept
that from you or the team.

18
00:00:35.122 --> 00:00:36.339
I am done looking for her.

19
00:00:36.340 --> 00:00:37.906
You don't want to find your mom?

20
00:00:37.907 --> 00:00:38.907
Welcome.

21
00:00:38.908 --> 00:00:42.737
My name is Noah Cyrus.

22
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:50.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

23
00:00:58.145 --> 00:00:59.667
Ooh. wait.

24
00:00:59.668 --> 00:01:01.147
Can you make one of those
heart design things?

25
00:01:01.148 --> 00:01:02.191
I want to post it.

26
00:01:02.192 --> 00:01:03.671
Maybe a star.

27
00:01:03.672 --> 00:01:06.630
No. wait. a flower.
like an orchid.

28
00:01:06.631 --> 00:01:09.416
They don't really teach us
how to do that.

29
00:01:09.417 --> 00:01:11.809
I can make a swirl.

30
00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:13.768
That's just so basic.

31
00:01:13.769 --> 00:01:16.553
Just try a flower.

32
00:01:16.554 --> 00:01:18.512
It's already half swirl.

33
00:01:18.513 --> 00:01:20.775
I mean. if you have to make
a fresh one. it's totally fine.

34
00:01:20.776 --> 00:01:21.819
I will pay for it.

35
00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:22.951
Do you mind?

36
00:01:22.952 --> 00:01:24.431
There are other people in line.

37
00:01:24.432 --> 00:01:26.607
Oh. shoot.

38
00:01:26.608 --> 00:01:28.870
Oh. my gosh. I forgot that
I have Hot Yoga in 15.

39
00:01:28.871 --> 00:01:30.001
Don't worry though.

40
00:01:30.002 --> 00:01:31.351
When I post this.
I'm going to totally

41
00:01:31.352 --> 00:01:32.614
make your cafe go viral.

42
00:01:35.269 --> 00:01:37.400
Sorry for that.
What can I get you?

43
00:01:37.401 --> 00:01:39.707
Hi. Drip coffee. please.

44
00:01:40.883 --> 00:01:42.318
TotesTina here.

45
00:01:42.319 --> 00:01:45.278
And it is time to reveal
the newest addition

46
00:01:45.279 --> 00:01:47.758
to Tina's Less to Impress list.

47
00:01:47.759 --> 00:01:49.978
First off.
I need you guys to go...

48
00:01:49.979 --> 00:01:51.719
no. not go. run...

49
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.287
to the cutest new coffee bar
I just found.

50
00:01:54.288 --> 00:01:55.897
Bernice's Coffee.

51
00:01:55.898 --> 00:01:58.769
No. seriously. people.
it's the best oat milk latte

52
00:01:58.770 --> 00:02:00.641
I've had all year.

53
00:02:00.642 --> 00:02:04.601
Whoever's feeling blessed.
say "blessed."

54
00:02:04.602 --> 00:02:07.300
Also. this new raspberry
lip gloss. ugh.

55
00:02:07.301 --> 00:02:08.997
it makes my lips just feel so...

56
00:02:21.402 --> 00:02:24.578
Hey. did Peck tell you
what this was all about?

57
00:02:24.579 --> 00:02:27.015
Uh. no. but when I get a call
to come to the Command Center.

58
00:02:27.016 --> 00:02:28.321
it's usually not for breakfast.

59
00:02:28.322 --> 00:02:29.322
Right. but when it's an inmate.

60
00:02:29.323 --> 00:02:31.889
I always get a heads up.

61
00:02:31.890 --> 00:02:33.021
You didn't?

62
00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:36.198
<i>As Agent Hasani will explain.</i>

63
00:02:36.199 --> 00:02:38.158
we have a problem.

64
00:02:39.246 --> 00:02:40.681
Last night. the convoy

65
00:02:40.682 --> 00:02:42.987
transporting Noah Cyrus
was attacked.

66
00:02:42.988 --> 00:02:46.339
Everyone. including Cyrus.
was killed.

67
00:02:47.819 --> 00:02:49.211
Do we know who did it?

68
00:02:49.212 --> 00:02:50.865
Why would somebody do this?

69
00:02:50.866 --> 00:02:52.910
Could have been one
of Cyrus' followers

70
00:02:52.911 --> 00:02:54.564
that we didn't know about?

71
00:02:54.565 --> 00:02:56.392
This is way too complicated
for someone of the 13th Hour.

72
00:02:56.393 --> 00:02:58.177
Who else knows
about the convoys?

73
00:02:58.178 --> 00:02:59.395
Just my people at CIA.

74
00:02:59.396 --> 00:03:02.355
Well. clearly. you're mistaken.

75
00:03:02.356 --> 00:03:04.618
Someone outside of this command

76
00:03:04.619 --> 00:03:07.055
knew exactly when
and where to ambush

77
00:03:07.056 --> 00:03:08.709
a covert prisoner transport.

78
00:03:08.710 --> 00:03:11.407
So either a member of your team
is talking

79
00:03:11.408 --> 00:03:12.887
or one of you is.

80
00:03:17.066 --> 00:03:18.284
Colonel...

81
00:03:18.285 --> 00:03:20.286
As it stands.
the Pentagon has insisted

82
00:03:20.287 --> 00:03:22.331
upon a certain balance of powers

83
00:03:22.332 --> 00:03:23.680
in the recovery efforts.

84
00:03:23.681 --> 00:03:26.596
So that means. Agent Hasani.

85
00:03:26.597 --> 00:03:28.468
prisoner transport
and relocation remains

86
00:03:28.469 --> 00:03:32.080
under your purview. for now.

87
00:03:32.081 --> 00:03:34.387
I don't think I need to
impress upon you all

88
00:03:34.388 --> 00:03:36.780
the seriousness
of this operational failure.

89
00:03:41.003 --> 00:03:42.699
Sorry to interrupt. Colonel.

90
00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:44.919
We just got a hit
on another inmate.

91
00:03:46.922 --> 00:03:48.575
No more mistakes.

92
00:03:48.576 --> 00:03:50.229
I expect perfection.

93
00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:51.230
Dismissed.

94
00:03:56.236 --> 00:03:59.194
Inmate H89. Lou Kaplan.

95
00:03:59.195 --> 00:04:01.327
A.K.A.. the Selfie Slayer.

96
00:04:01.328 --> 00:04:03.154
Not to brag. but low-key.

97
00:04:03.155 --> 00:04:05.766
I created a program
to alert me if any inmates.

98
00:04:05.767 --> 00:04:08.116
logged on to their dormant
social media platforms.

99
00:04:08.117 --> 00:04:09.813
Wow. that's very clever.

100
00:04:09.814 --> 00:04:11.206
Thank you.

101
00:04:11.207 --> 00:04:13.034
It uses malware software
I designed to bypass VPNs.

102
00:04:13.035 --> 00:04:16.777
It looks like Lou just
logged on to his old

103
00:04:16.778 --> 00:04:20.128
SnapMax account
for the first time since 2019

104
00:04:20.129 --> 00:04:21.825
in Midtown Manhattan.

105
00:04:21.826 --> 00:04:24.611
I guess even Pit inmates
can't stay off social media.

106
00:04:24.612 --> 00:04:25.873
SnapMax.
that's the one that's. like.

107
00:04:25.874 --> 00:04:27.614
if Instagram and TikTok
had a baby. right?

108
00:04:27.615 --> 00:04:29.268
Well. I don't know.

109
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.922
We have a strict no social
media policy at my house.

110
00:04:31.923 --> 00:04:33.184
That's fun.

111
00:04:33.185 --> 00:04:35.361
It says here that Lou
was a gifted coder

112
00:04:35.362 --> 00:04:37.972
and one of the original
software designers for SnapMax.

113
00:04:37.973 --> 00:04:40.844
He had some pretty lofty ideals
about social media

114
00:04:40.845 --> 00:04:43.630
fostering community and empathy.

115
00:04:43.631 --> 00:04:45.327
I'm sensing a turn coming.

116
00:04:45.328 --> 00:04:47.111
Well. he wanted his technology

117
00:04:47.112 --> 00:04:48.461
to bring people together.

118
00:04:48.462 --> 00:04:50.898
Instead. according to him.
the app. quote.

119
00:04:50.899 --> 00:04:53.814
"Became a breeding ground
for vanity. vitriol.

120
00:04:53.815 --> 00:04:56.773
and self-isolating behavior."

121
00:04:56.774 --> 00:04:59.298
So I'm guessing the nickname
the Selfie Slayer

122
00:04:59.299 --> 00:05:00.342
is not a metaphor.

123
00:05:00.343 --> 00:05:01.561
His M.O. is interesting.

124
00:05:01.562 --> 00:05:02.997
Despite the fact
that he carefully selected

125
00:05:02.998 --> 00:05:05.129
and then stalked
these victims for days.

126
00:05:05.130 --> 00:05:07.349
the kills themselves
were semi-improvised

127
00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:09.046
and always public.

128
00:05:09.047 --> 00:05:11.310
This one.
he threw into oncoming traffic

129
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:12.615
as she was livestreaming.

130
00:05:12.616 --> 00:05:13.747
And then another.
he beat to death

131
00:05:13.748 --> 00:05:16.097
in Prospect Park
using his own tripod.

132
00:05:16.098 --> 00:05:18.099
He claimed that
his six murders were a message.

133
00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:19.535
a way to wake the world up
to the dangers

134
00:05:19.536 --> 00:05:20.710
of social media.

135
00:05:20.711 --> 00:05:22.669
The Post wrote
a whole exposé on him.

136
00:05:22.670 --> 00:05:25.411
turning him into a social media
sensation himself.

137
00:05:25.412 --> 00:05:27.848
an ironic poster child
for disruption.

138
00:05:27.849 --> 00:05:29.719
They even had merch
with his face on it

139
00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:31.547
outside the courthouse
during his trial.

140
00:05:31.548 --> 00:05:32.548
- Gross.
- Gross.

141
00:05:32.549 --> 00:05:33.854
- Gross.
- Yeah.

142
00:05:33.855 --> 00:05:35.508
If he's already logged
back into SnapMax again.

143
00:05:35.509 --> 00:05:37.510
he's probably stalking victims.

144
00:05:37.511 --> 00:05:39.512
Let's head out.

145
00:05:42.385 --> 00:05:44.908
OK. time to shine.

146
00:05:46.998 --> 00:05:48.434
Just remember. be bright.

147
00:05:48.435 --> 00:05:49.826
Be bold.

148
00:05:49.827 --> 00:05:51.959
Be Becky.

149
00:05:53.396 --> 00:05:56.006
Ahh.

150
00:05:58.183 --> 00:06:00.054
Hello. fellow bakers.

151
00:06:00.055 --> 00:06:02.230
It's your friend.
Baking with Becky.

152
00:06:02.231 --> 00:06:04.667
And today. I've got
a big treat for you all.

153
00:06:04.668 --> 00:06:07.453
We're making banana nut muffins.

154
00:06:07.454 --> 00:06:09.324
Now.

155
00:06:09.325 --> 00:06:11.413
I know these look a bit ripe.

156
00:06:11.414 --> 00:06:12.458
Don't you worry.

157
00:06:12.459 --> 00:06:14.764
That's the secret to yum.

158
00:06:14.765 --> 00:06:16.636
But before we start.
I want to make sure

159
00:06:16.637 --> 00:06:18.551
you hit that Subscribe button
to stay in the loop

160
00:06:18.552 --> 00:06:20.335
for all my best new recipes.

161
00:06:20.336 --> 00:06:22.903
All right. it's baking time.

162
00:06:22.904 --> 00:06:24.905
Now. you're gonna want to start

163
00:06:24.906 --> 00:06:27.951
with two cups
of all-purpose flour.

164
00:06:29.911 --> 00:06:33.130
Next. we're gonna crack
two eggs.

165
00:06:35.133 --> 00:06:37.613
Damn it.

166
00:06:42.445 --> 00:06:44.794
Take seven.

167
00:06:58.592 --> 00:07:00.723
You guys get the feeling
Lazarus knows more

168
00:07:00.724 --> 00:07:04.248
about this convoy hit
than she's letting on?

169
00:07:04.249 --> 00:07:07.513
I mean. her pointing fingers
at us is definitely theater.

170
00:07:07.514 --> 00:07:09.166
She knows something.

171
00:07:09.167 --> 00:07:10.864
So do I.

172
00:07:10.865 --> 00:07:13.519
Cyrus's convoy deviated from
its planned route last night.

173
00:07:15.609 --> 00:07:17.566
Maybe they saw
the attack coming?

174
00:07:17.567 --> 00:07:21.831
Well. there was no report of
contact before the firefight.

175
00:07:21.832 --> 00:07:24.355
OK. so now we have
two mysteries...

176
00:07:24.356 --> 00:07:26.314
who attacked the convoy

177
00:07:26.315 --> 00:07:28.577
and how it got deviated
in the first place.

178
00:07:46.378 --> 00:07:48.510
What comes next?

179
00:07:48.511 --> 00:07:50.556
The eggs?

180
00:07:50.557 --> 00:07:53.036
Then why are you looking at me?

181
00:07:53.037 --> 00:07:54.429
Crack the eggs.

182
00:08:12.317 --> 00:08:13.710
Bravo.

183
00:08:15.756 --> 00:08:17.191
OK. now say it.

184
00:08:22.937 --> 00:08:24.198
Ah!

185
00:08:26.897 --> 00:08:28.594
Becky.

186
00:08:28.595 --> 00:08:31.248
say it.

187
00:08:31.249 --> 00:08:33.208
OK.

188
00:08:34.731 --> 00:08:36.732
Hi. everyone.

189
00:08:36.733 --> 00:08:39.039
This is gonna be my final post.

190
00:09:02.019 --> 00:09:03.629
I want to try
to put this in terms

191
00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:07.807
that someone as simple
as you can understand.

192
00:09:07.808 --> 00:09:12.463
I had the biggest tech
companies in the entire world

193
00:09:12.464 --> 00:09:15.292
engaged in heated bidding wars

194
00:09:15.293 --> 00:09:17.643
to bring me to their teams. right?

195
00:09:17.644 --> 00:09:19.601
Instead. I chose SnapMax.

196
00:09:19.602 --> 00:09:21.647
a no-name startup.

197
00:09:21.648 --> 00:09:24.737
because I believed
in their mission.

198
00:09:24.738 --> 00:09:27.348
Also. Linda Cranston
personally came to my home

199
00:09:27.349 --> 00:09:29.785
and practically begged me
on her hands and knees

200
00:09:29.786 --> 00:09:31.700
to work for her.

201
00:09:31.701 --> 00:09:35.617
<i>We designed SnapMax as a tool
to help our users connect.</i>

202
00:09:35.618 --> 00:09:39.012
<i>But after SnapMax launched.
a very unfortunate truth</i>

203
00:09:39.013 --> 00:09:41.144
<i>became abundantly clear to me...</i>

204
00:09:41.145 --> 00:09:45.409
<i>most people are basically rats.</i>

205
00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:47.542
<i>But it's worse than that
because we have</i>

206
00:09:47.543 --> 00:09:50.850
<i>the intellectual capacity.</i>

207
00:09:50.851 --> 00:09:54.114
<i>but we don't use it.</i>

208
00:09:54.115 --> 00:09:56.856
<i>All the likes. and the clicks.
and the comments.</i>

209
00:09:56.857 --> 00:09:58.292
<i>and the shares.</i>

210
00:09:58.293 --> 00:10:01.295
<i>jonesing for another hit
of dopamine. right?</i>

211
00:10:01.296 --> 00:10:02.688
<i>Just click. click.
click. click. click.</i>

212
00:10:02.689 --> 00:10:04.298
<i>just for dopamine.</i>

213
00:10:04.299 --> 00:10:05.560
<i>Just a little hit.</i>

214
00:10:05.561 --> 00:10:08.389
<i>Tell me.
are you on social media?</i>

215
00:10:08.390 --> 00:10:10.652
<i>Yeah. of course you are.</i>

216
00:10:10.653 --> 00:10:12.567
This guy seems like
a real winner.

217
00:10:12.568 --> 00:10:13.568
Yeah.

218
00:10:13.569 --> 00:10:15.352
Hey. how can you be so whiny

219
00:10:15.353 --> 00:10:17.006
and crazy at the same time?

220
00:10:17.007 --> 00:10:18.878
Oh. it's a skill.

221
00:10:18.879 --> 00:10:20.401
Did you guys know his account

222
00:10:20.402 --> 00:10:22.664
has 10 million followers
on SnapMax?

223
00:10:22.665 --> 00:10:23.970
Huh.

224
00:10:23.971 --> 00:10:25.754
World thinks this guy's
been dead for years.

225
00:10:25.755 --> 00:10:27.626
Still. he has more followers
than the people he's killed.

226
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:29.845
You know. I'm all aboard
the social media's

227
00:10:29.846 --> 00:10:31.412
destroying society train.

228
00:10:31.413 --> 00:10:33.370
but it's not a cause
worthy of murder.

229
00:10:33.371 --> 00:10:36.330
Lou rationalized his murders
through his message.

230
00:10:36.331 --> 00:10:38.419
He warned people the dangers
of social media.

231
00:10:38.420 --> 00:10:40.334
He thought it was a just cause.

232
00:10:40.335 --> 00:10:41.509
which is why his therapist
at the Pit

233
00:10:41.510 --> 00:10:42.989
tried to humanize his victims.

234
00:10:42.990 --> 00:10:44.947
Just or not. these were people.

235
00:10:44.948 --> 00:10:46.470
That tracks.

236
00:10:46.471 --> 00:10:48.951
Kaplan's file says he was
given Whitmore's empathy drug.

237
00:10:48.952 --> 00:10:50.257
I've seen a lot of that.

238
00:10:50.258 --> 00:10:52.259
It was effective.

239
00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:54.000
so long as
he maintained his dosage.

240
00:10:54.001 --> 00:10:55.131
Well. it must have worn off.

241
00:10:55.132 --> 00:10:56.611
Morales got a ping
on a body drop

242
00:10:56.612 --> 00:10:58.221
four blocks from
where he logged in.

243
00:11:09.799 --> 00:11:12.932
Why is the DEA so interested
in a dead influencer?

244
00:11:12.933 --> 00:11:14.368
Oh. um.

245
00:11:14.369 --> 00:11:16.762
Becky Roman is actually
an undercover informant

246
00:11:16.763 --> 00:11:19.939
for a sting operation
we're running.

247
00:11:19.940 --> 00:11:22.463
If you say so. buddy.

248
00:11:22.464 --> 00:11:25.074
Any details on cause of death?

249
00:11:25.075 --> 00:11:26.815
Asphyxiation.

250
00:11:26.816 --> 00:11:29.296
Death by banana muffin.

251
00:11:29.297 --> 00:11:32.255
That's definitely a new one.

252
00:11:32.256 --> 00:11:35.781
Well. we're gonna need the
place to ourselves there. pal.

253
00:11:37.044 --> 00:11:38.348
Thank you.

254
00:11:45.095 --> 00:11:46.705
OK.

255
00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:48.924
So Becky was clearly
in the middle of making a video

256
00:11:48.925 --> 00:11:50.317
when Lou killed her.

257
00:11:50.318 --> 00:11:54.060
That speaks to
his old M.O.. but...

258
00:11:54.061 --> 00:11:55.278
all of his previous kills

259
00:11:55.279 --> 00:11:57.977
were quick and improvised...

260
00:11:57.978 --> 00:12:00.196
and public.

